\par }{\cf0 Incantation Definitions
\par }{\fs20\cf0 The following terms are used extensively in this section
\par of the chapter:
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Incantation: }{\fs20\cf0 Powerful ritual magic that requires successful Knowledge (arcane lore) checks to cast. Incantations don\rquote t require spellcasting ability, don\rquote t take up spell slots, can\rquote 
t be improved using metamagic feats, and need not be prepared ahead of time. 
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Factor: }{\fs20\cf0 An aspect of the incantation that\rquote s built in when the incantation is designed. Casters have no control over factors; they\rquote 
re an indelible part of the incantation. When a GM designs an incantation, factors are useful ways to customize an incantation.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Option: }{\fs20\cf0 Aspects of the incantation that make it easier or harder, depending on choices the caster makes. Options provide modifiers to the caster\rquote s Knowledge (arcane lore) check.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Seed: }{\fs20\cf0 The building blocks of incantation, seeds describe magical effects in general terms.
